ring this up is PM had Fear yesterday, had problems, CT was up... they called in BoD, which is great, I commend them for that... However, from what I've gathered, BoD had a few problems themselves, and didn't leave the plane til after 8 this morning. In fact, I just walked around Fear, and there were no mobs up, and several BoD bodies, full clothed, scattered around. Ros' Fear raid is scheduled to start in a little over an hour... and there's nothing up to kill.<br>
<br>
I submit that the 2am deadline applies to BB guilds as well as the regularly scheduled guilds, and in the future, everyone needs to respect it, or risk the chance of ruining someone else's raid, as our raid today has been.<br>
<br>
Thorfinn Wayforger<br>
Guild Leader<br>
Requiem of Souls <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedwinanytengayle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EdwinaNytengayle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RTA Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/29/00 1:22:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868/Ed.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Policy Question</span><hr size=1> This is not the first instance I've heard about the posting guild calling in BB and staying until the next morning.  I would agree that folks need to be out at a reasonable time.  BoD *could* have been called in late (I've been out of the loop and am trying to catch up), but this situation needs to be addressed, and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> soon</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.   <p><B><FONT FACE="Tahoma" COLOR="#ffffff">Edwina Nytengayle<BR>
<I>54<SUP>th</SUP> Cleric</B><BR></I></FONT>
<A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868"><I><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff">Knights of Phoenix</I></FONT></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthorfinnwayforger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorfinn Wayforger</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wog</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/3/01 10:01:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Policy Question</span><hr size=1> I agree Edwina, but you're the only person who responded here, and it took you 11 days, so long I'd quit checking for a reply... I posted here, because I didn't want to see the arguments that occurred when this went public. I'd still like some resolution though... Which calendar has precedence? the &quot;regular&quot; one? or the &quot;Epic&quot; one? If the regular one, then the BB/Epic guild really should be out by 2am PST as well... if the Epic one, then I guess they stay as long as they have to, and a few raids get ruined... I could live with it either way, I guess, but I really feel it needs to be nailed down, otherwise much bad blood could result. <p>The Forger of the Way<BR>
